HEADLINE: Data Centre Engineering Operations Chief Engineer, ARN- DCEO
DESCRIPTION__TEXT:
As Chief Engineer, you will be responsible for ensuring that all electrical, mechanical, and fire/life safety equipment within the data center is operating at peak efficiency. This involves planned preventative maintenance of equipment, daily corrective work, and emergency response. You are expected to be a singular focal point for all facility operations and to support Amazon within its owned and operated data centers. You should be able to manage large scale impacting projects and new region support from conception to completion. These projects involve large amounts of independent work as well as collaboration with external support groups including engineering, automation, procurement, and finance in both local and global settings. 
As Chief Engineer, you will be tasked with creating and delivering on key milestones, obtaining and tracking quotes for all necessary costs, and documenting project results for future implementation at other facilities. The goals of such projects are for the Chief Engineers to drive innovation and resiliency while reducing operational costs in the facilities. 
AWS Infrastructure Services (AIS) AWS Infrastructure Services owns the design, planning, delivery, and operation of all AWS global infrastructure. In other words, we’re the people who keep the cloud running. We support all AWS data centers and all of the servers, storage, networking, power, and cooling equipment that ensure our customers have continual access to the innovation they rely on. We work on the most challenging problems, with thousands of variables impacting the supply chain — and we’re looking for talented people who want to help. 
You’ll join a diverse team of software, hardware, and network engineers, supply chain specialists, security experts, operations managers, and other vital roles. You’ll collaborate with people across AWS to help us deliver the highest standards for safety and security while providing seemingly infinite capacity at the lowest possible cost for our customers. And you’ll experience an inclusive culture that welcomes bold ideas and empowers you to own them to completion. 
Key job responsibilities 
• Train and support the Engineering team in their role of providing electrical and mechanical equipment troubleshooting and operations 
• Implement and execute site or equipment-specific training exercises. Exercises cover, but are not limited to: stand-by diesel generators, switchgear, UPSs, PDUs, AHUs, chillers etc. 
• Oversee day-to-day operation and maintenance of mechanical and electrical equipment in data center sites 
• Operate independently, with limited direct management 
• Assist in the design and build-out of new facilities and perform root cause analysis of equipment failures 
• Act as an escalation point for all facilities-related issues within the data center region. Work OT hours as needed to support site stability 
• Troubleshoot and report facility and data sever-level events within internal Service Level Agreements (SLA) 
• Create and deploy standard practices for Engineering Operations Technicians, Chief Engineers, and vendor support teams 
• Ensure all safety procedures are adhered to by vendors, and AWS staff PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS 
• Work at height, and from ladders 
• Perform physical tasks during the shift 
• Work in a noisy environment, with ear protection 
A day in the life 
Working semi-autonomously in operation and maintenance of mechanical and electrical equipment in a data center Execution of project scopes of basic complexity Providing timely escalation for all facilities-related issues within the data center First-line troubleshooting and reporting of facility and high-criticality events within a pre-determined service level agreement (SLA) Providing assistance to junior and peer EOTs Oversight of third-party vendors to ensure that all work performed is in accordance with established safety protocols, best practices, and local legislation Utilization of administrative tools for change management, ticketing, and asset management. Flexibility for changes to work schedule depending on specific site needs. Shifts can be up to 12-hours and may rotate on a predefined schedule. 
About the team 
Diverse Experiences AWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying. 
Why AWS? 
Amazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses. 
Inclusive Team Culture 
Here at AWS, it’s in our nature to learn and be curious. Our employee-led affinity groups foster a culture of inclusion that empower us to be proud of our differences. Ongoing events and learning experiences, including our Conversations on Race and Ethnicity (CORE) and AmazeCon (gender diversity) conferences, inspire us to never stop embracing our uniqueness. 
Mentorship & Career Growth 
We’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional. 
Work/Life Balance 
We value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.
Basic Qualifications
- Bachelor Degree in electrical or mechanical engineering or equivalent - NVQ Level 3 in Electrical/Mechanical Engineering (or equivalent) 
- 3+ years of Data Centre Engineering/Operations Experience
Preferred Qualifications
- 6+ years of experience in operations and on-call support for Data Center facilities or Mission Critical Plants/Production facilities 
- High/Low Voltage Authorised Person (AP) experience 
- Fundamental knowledge of network design and layout as well as low voltage (copper/ fibre) cabling 
- Project Management experience

If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.

Why AWS?

Amazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.

Inclusive Team Culture

Here at AWS, it’s in our nature to learn and be curious. Our employee-led affinity groups foster a culture of inclusion that empower us to be proud of our differences. Ongoing events and learning experiences, including our Conversations on Race and Ethnicity (CORE) and AmazeCon (gender diversity) conferences, inspire us to never stop embracing our uniqueness.

Mentorship & Career Growth

We’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.

Work/Life Balance

We value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.

Basic Qualifications

- Bachelor Degree in electrical or mechanical engineering or equivalent - NVQ Level 3 in Electrical/Mechanical Engineering (or equivalent)

- 3+ years of Data Centre Engineering/Operations Experience

Preferred Qualifications

- 6+ years of experience in operations and on-call support for Data Center facilities or Mission Critical Plants/Production facilities

- High/Low Voltage Authorised Person (AP) experience

- Fundamental knowledge of network design and layout as well as low voltage (copper/ fibre) cabling

- Project Management experience

HEADLINE: Data & Evaluation Engineer - Video Analytics, Lund
DESCRIPTION__TEXT:
At Axis Communications, we don't just create cameras - we create world-leading intelligent systems that understand what they see to keep people safe. Our advanced analytics analyses video streams in real time, powering surveillance and safety applications worldwide. We are now looking for a hands-on, senior computer vision Data & Evaluation Engineer to join our Analytics team in Lund, Sweden. Is that you? 

Your future team
One of Axis greatest assets is our culture with a strong focus on collaboration. We know that good ideas can come anytime and anywhere and therefore we encourage everyone to contribute and be innovative. If you are a person who likes to make a difference, you will feel right at home with us! We want you to enjoy working with us and we believe team spirit, collaboration, learning, equal opportunities for all and having fun are central parts in this.

What You'll Do
This opportunity is all about understanding the functionality and accuracy of our analytics use case solutions. To ensure our solutions perform at their best you will be responsible for evaluating AI model and use case accuracy performance on real-world scenario data set coverage and key metrics. You will craft, curate and maintain the essential video evaluation datasets and metrics for scene and use case coverage. For this, you will also, define, update, and implement annotation guidelines that are clear, consistent, and reflect diverse real-world conditions to ensure consistent, reliable ground truth for evaluation. We want you to take charge of annotation quality control, working hands-on with tools like CVAT and collaborating with annotators.

This isn't a role where you hand down specs and walk away. This is about being in the engine room - building the data sets from the ground up, ensuring they are relevant, structured, accurate, and reflective of the real world in all its complexity. Think edge cases, shifting light, moving shadows... Advocate for dataset completeness and scenario coverage, ensuring AI models, algorithms and use cases are tested against real-world edge cases and safety-critical events. You will evaluate and analyze AI model outputs, algorithms and use case accuracy performance using your curated datasets and key metrics - accuracy, precision, recall, confusion matrix, false positive/negative rates, product metrics etc - to uncover strengths and opportunities. You won't be training AI models from scratch but will work closely with machine learning engineers and algorithm developers to translate evaluation insights into validated and improved use case performance. As such you will contribute to data-driven AI model, algorithm and use case debugging, identifying whether errors stem from data gaps or algorithm limitations.

Who are you?
You believe that great analytics solutions depend on appropriate data validation and evaluation - and that the details matter. You bring deep experience as data scientist or similar, designing and working with video analytics datasets, preferably in safety-critical or surveillance contexts. You are skilled in accuracy performance evaluation of analytics use cases and have practical knowledge of evaluation metrics and best practices for AI model, algorithm and use case testing and validation.

You are detail-oriented and hands-on, driven to translate evaluation data into actionable insights. You are comfortable diving into annotations both in terms of crafting guidelines and working with tools e.g. CVAT or developing internally crafted tools if that better suits the needs at hand. You are software savvy and can pick up a language like Python or dashboard tool without issue. You thrive in collaborative environments and know the power of bridging data, evaluation, and algorithm development.

Most importantly, you want to work somewhere that values your expertise and encourages inclusivity, mentorship, and continuous learning. In our team you will not only be an exceptional data and evaluation engineer but also a mentor and coach who can inspire and grow our team.

What Axis has to offer
We are a world leader in network video, where cutting-edge technology meets global impact. Here, you'll contribute to meaningful projects that shape the future of security and surveillance - developing solutions used worldwide. As a fast-growing company, we offer exciting career opportunities. You'll grow professionally through continuous learning, supported by a collaborative team that values creativity, innovation, and work-life balance.

Our Lund HQ Campus, including the impressive Grenden building, offers a dynamic environment with spaces crafted to encourage collaboration, whether through informal "fika" chats, formal meetings, or after-hours activities. Check it out: Axis HQ

Your well-being matters to us. We offer a range of benefits, including a company bonus, Friday cake, wellness allowance, health insurance - and even your own Axis bicycle.

To learn more about Axis, our innovative products, solutions, and vibrant company culture, explore:
Life at Axis blog
Engineering at Axis blog
Innovation at Axis

Ready to Act?
If you're ready to apply your skills in video data and evaluation of analytics solutions systems and work with a diverse, innovative team, we want to hear from you.

Apply today or get in touch with me, , for an informal conversation. Let's build a safer, smarter world - together.

HEADLINE: Senior Software Engineer - Data & Video Analytics, Lund
DESCRIPTION__TEXT:
In the open office landscape, you look around the room and see others who share your passion. Emersed in focused coding or in a soft tuned dialogue you are a team of innovators, working together to create a smarter, safer world. Your teammate meets your eye with a smile and you decide to go for a freshly brewed coffee. Returning to your desks feeling refreshed and focused you dive back into problem solving with renewed vigor and a shared enthusiasm. Ideas flows freely, and the collective energy is palpable. Welcome to Axis Analytics solutions - a place where passion met purpose, and every day presents an opportunity to make a positive impact.

Your future team
Inside Axis Analytics Solutions, we're a team of engineers who collaborate seamlessly for data-driven development and evaluation of our analytics solutions. Our scope includes data curation, algorithm development and evaluation as well as a toolchain to support our everyday activities.

One of Axis greatest assets is our culture with a strong focus on collaboration. We know that good ideas can come anytime and anywhere and therefore we encourage everyone to contribute and be innovative. If you are a person who likes to make a difference, you will feel right at home with us! As a member of our team, you'll enjoy a culture that encourages collaboration, learning, and growth. We want you to enjoy working with us and we believe team spirit, equal opportunities for all and having fun are central parts in this.

Your Role: A Hands-On Software Architect
To complement our existing strengths, we are looking for you to join our crew and bring your own unique approach and experiences all the while respecting Axis core values - Act as one, Always open, Think big. As a senior software engineer, you'll be instrumental in designing and implementing full-stack scalable solutions, from concept to delivery. Together we will tackle complex system issues, and your expertise in design patterns, software product architecture, and Kubernetes will be invaluable. In our team you will not only be an exceptional coder but also a mentor and leader who can inspire and grow our team. We want you to contribute across our scope and be happy to chip in where you are needed the most. Whether it is to enhance our tools for evaluation, visualization and annotation or our algorithm product solutions.

Who are you?
Although we do not know you yet, we believe you are a person who is trustworthy and respected in your professional role. We expect you thrive when collaborating with your team and are experienced, pragmatic and proactive in suggesting solutions to the technical challenges we are tackling. We hope you are curious and passionate in the production of high quality, robust and reusable code and someone who has built software products from design to validation. Continuous improvement is important to you and it's natural for you to share your knowledge so that we learn alongside you and you with us.

More concretely, we would like you to bring:

 * Excellence in Python and perhaps some C++ on Linux platforms
 * Strong professionalism in design patterns and clean coding
 * Practical knowledge of SW system design and architecture
 * Familiarity with Docker, Kubernetes and Git
 * Understanding of database and event systems
 * Excellent collaboration and communication with fluency in English and Swedish is a bonus

It would also be nice if you have some:

 * Frontend development experience with React
 * Knowledge of cameras, web, and cloud technologies
 * Experience in computer vision and video analytics software and some insights into Artificial Intelligence libraries

What Axis has to offer
We are a world leader in network video, where cutting-edge technology meets global impact. Here, you'll contribute to meaningful projects that shape the future of security and surveillance - developing solutions used worldwide. As a fast-growing company, we offer exciting career opportunities. You'll grow professionally through continuous learning, supported by a collaborative team that values creativity, innovation, and work-life balance.

Our Lund HQ Campus, including the impressive Grenden building, offers a dynamic environment with spaces crafted to encourage collaboration, whether through informal "fika" chats, formal meetings, or after-hours activities. Check it out: Axis HQ

Your well-being matters to us. We offer a range of benefits, including a company bonus, Friday cake, wellness allowance, health insurance - and even your own Axis bicycle.

To learn more about Axis, our innovative products, solutions, and vibrant company culture, explore:
Life at Axis blog
Engineering at Axis blog
Innovation at Axis

Ready to Act?
Apply today to become part of our close-knit team of innovators, working together to create cutting-edge software solutions that make a real difference. You will be surrounded by talented individuals who share your drive and enthusiasm, and together, we will shape a safer, smarter world.

Reach out to me, , your future manager, if you have any questions. I look forward to hear from you and welcome you to the team.
